        "sha": "17d3cb6e19fab3c874110fa03e2a04aaa9485c07",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/17d3cb6e19fab3c874110fa03e2a04aaa9485c07"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 17d3cb6e19fab3c874110fa03e2a04aaa9485c07\nparent d406cffafdd111b34dc613b4cb82b4f0a264d225\nauthor CruzMolina <7537712+CruzMolina@users.noreply.github.com> 1778274514 -0700\ncommitter CruzMolina <7537712+CruzMolina@users.noreply.github.com> 1778274514 -0700\n\ndbwrapper: avoid value copy when unobfuscated\n\nCDBIterator::GetValue() currently copies the current LevelDB value into a DataStream before deserializing it, even when the database is not obfuscated.\n\nUse SpanReader in the no-obfuscation case so the value bytes are read directly from the iterator span. Keep the existing DataStream path when obfuscation is enabled, because that path needs a mutable owning buffer.\n\nExtend the iterator test to cover failed value deserialization without consuming the current iterator entry.\n",
